fields.physical_description:
1. farmer; polished and oiled wood. A standing figure with arms which move up and down; it is carved from a single block of wood with a dividing line to indicate the legs and three black dots to represent the eyes and mouth. 4 x 1¼ x 1 5/8in (£3.20) 
2. cat; polished and oiled yew wood. It is carved from a single block of wood. 1 3/4 x 1 3/4 x 5/8in ((1.00) 
3. cat; polished and oiled walnut. As above. (£1.00) 
4. dog; polished and oiled walnut. It is carved from a single block of wood and has the appearance of a Border Collie. 3 x 1½ x 5/8in (£1.15) 5. cockerel; polished and oiled reddish wood. It is carved from a single
block of yew wood. 1 3/4 x 2 x ½in (£1.05) 
6. hen; upright; polished and oiled wood. It is carved from a single block of wood. 1½ x 1 3/4 x 5/8in (75p.) 
7. hen; pecking; polished and oiled wood. It is carved from a single block of wood. 2 x 1½ x 5/8in (75p.) 
8. sow; polished and oiled ash wood. It is carved from a single block of wood with a twine tail. 3 1/8 x 2 x 3/4in (£1.65) 
9. piglet; polished and oiled ash wood with twine tail. It is carved from a single block of wood. 1½ x 1 x ½in (90p.) 
10. piglet; as above but made from walnut. (90p.) 
11. goat; large; polished and oiled dark wood; walnut. It is carved from a single block. 3 3/8 x 3 1/8 x 3/4in (£1.40) 
12. goat; medium; polished and oiled yew wood. It is carved from a  single block of reddish wood. 3 x 2 5/8 x 5/8in (£1.10)
13. goat; kid; polished and oiled ash wood. It is carved from a single block of pale yellow wood. 2 x 2 x ½in (75p.) 
14. donkey; polished and oiled wood; probably oak. It is carved from a single block of wood with a twine tail. 3½ x 3 x 3/4in (£1.60) 
15. horse; polished and oiled yew wood. It is carved from a single block of wood. 4½ x 4 x 3/4in (£1.80) 
16. horse; polished and oiled ash wood. It is carved from a block of  wood with a teased hessian tail. 4½ x 4 x 3/4in (£1.90) 
17. horse; as above but from oak. 4½ x 4 x 3/4in (£2.05) 
18. foal; polished and oiled wood; probably yew. It is carved from a block of wood with a teased hessian tail. 3 x 3 x 5/8in (£1.60) 
19. bull; polished and oiled yew wood. It is carved from a single block of reddish wood with the horns of a very pale wood, glued on and the tail of a piece of twine. 4¼ x 3 x 1in (£2.10) 
20. cow; polished and oiled walnut wood. It is carved from a single block of wood with lighter wood horns and a twine tail. 3 7/8 x 3 x 3/4in (£1.80) 21. cow; polished and oiled yew wood. It is as above. (£1.80) 
22. cow; polished and oiled yew wood. It is grazing. 3½ x 2 5/8 x 3/4in (£1.80) 
23. calf; polished and oiled yew wood. It is carved from a single block of wood with a twine tail. 2½ x 2 x 5/8in (£1.60) 
24. sheep; carved wood painted off white with a black head and feet. 2 5/8 x 2¼ x 5/8in (£1.70) 
25. sheep grazing; painted off white with a black head and feet and dark brown felt ears. 2½ x 1 7/8 x 5/8in (£1.80) 
26. lamb; standing; carved wood painted off white with dark brown felt ears. 1 3/4 x 1 3/4 x ½in (£1.15) 
27. lamb; lying down; carved wood painted off white with dark brown felt ears. 1½ x 7/8 x ½in (£1.15) 
28. duck; sitting; carved wood painted off white with an orange beak. 
1 3/4 x 1½ x ½in (£1.00) 
29. duck; standing; carved wood painted off white with an orange beak. 2¼ x 1½ x ½in (£1.00) 
30. goose; standing; carved wood painted off white with an orange beak. 1½ x 2 5/8 x ½in (£1.15) 
31. goose; hissing; carved wood paianted off white with an orange beak. 3¼ x 1 x ½in (£1.15) 
32. deer; polished and oiled yew wood. It is carved from a single block of reddish wood with the antlers of a pale wood; glued to the head. 3½ x 4¼ x 3/4in (£3.45) 
33. badger; polished and oiled wood; walnut and a very light wood. It is carved from a single block of wood with the facial stripes added. 4 x 1¼ x 3/4in (£2.65) 
34. otter; polished and oiled wood; light brown with a very pale piece inserted under the head. 4¼ x 1¼ x 3/4in (£2.45)
35. fox; polished and oiled yew wood. It is carved from one block of  wood. 4¼ x 1 x 5/8in (£1.15) 
36. hare; polished and oiled reddished wood. It is carved from one block of yew wood. 1½ x 2 x ½in (£1.35) 
37. squirrel; polished and oiled wood. It is carved from one block of wood and shaped to appear to be holding a nut between its front feet. 3 x 3/4 x ½in (£1.35) 
38. rabbit; polished and oiled wood. It is carved from a single block of wood. 1½ x 1 x ½in (£1.00)
39. gate and stile; polished and oiled wood. It is a three barred gate hinged with brass pins to a stile. 8 5/8 x 3¼ x 1 1/8in (£3.50) 
40. hedge; painted green. It is wavy both along its length and along the top edge. 8 3/8 x 1 3/4 x 3/8in (£1.00) 
41. hedge; polished and oiled wood. It is the same as the painted hedge. (90p.) 
42. bridge; polished and oiled wood. It is created from a single block of wood. 7 x 1 3/4in x 2¼in (£3.50) 
43. wall; various coloured blocks of wood; polished and oiled; designed to represent a dry stone wall; top edge is rounded. 7 3/4 x 12 x 3/4in (2.45) 
44. tree; natural wood polished and oiled. It is carved in two parts. 5 7/8 x 4½ x 1in (£3.75) 
45. tree; wood painted green at the top with the trunk a plain light wood. 5 7/8 x 4½ x 1in. (£4.15)
